metadata.name: Abstract Memories #231
metadata.description:
I try to explore the unknown nature of objects in an emotional abstraction. Instead of imposing an entirely personal feeling on the canvas, I draw something out of the canvas with the tools of expressive abstraction and color contrast. The content of an abstract painting completely bypasses all those mental filters. Abstract painting is the revelation of the inner life of the human soul; it transforms from words to visual identity. The abstract painting speaks the language of the imaginary world, a language that struggles with complexities.
I have always been interested in laying out patterns on the flat surface of the canvas and deciding how to cut and relate the frame to those elements on my design page. This focus is created through the influence of unpredictable handprints, batik prints, watercolors, and other oriental objects in my works. The desire for this decorative approach led me to cut the three-dimensional environment into a repeating flat pattern so that the rhythm of the shapes emphasizes the strong structure. Also, my attempt to use contrasting colors right next to each other - warm reds and oranges against great neutral greens, blues, and grays - is influenced by the challenging thinking of color and the lightness of impressionism in my work, where pure colors "in a reflection in mind And the contrast makes them even more vivid. They are precisely like the works we enjoy in the real world of reflected light. They can be easily overlooked in the dull colors of a canvas or on a productive work page; these contrasts and complementary color silences side by side. , create a magnificent symphony of colors.

Instead of imposing an entirely personal feeling on the canvas, I draw something out of the canvas with the tools of expressive abstraction and color contrast. The content of an abstract painting completely bypasses all those mental filters. Abstract painting is the revelation of the inner life of the human soul; it transforms from words to visual identity. The abstract painting speaks the language of the imaginary world, a language that struggles with complexities.
These types of art provide humanity with a background voice that profoundly soothes and heals our souls precisely because it is not figurative and, therefore, malleable and defined visually. An abstract painter seeks to depict the world around us in a way that is not what we see, but the message is that "this is what the world feels like." An abstract work puts the viewer in a position to create an interactive experience with the art by giving them the freedom to say, "this is for me."Looking at this work, we see pieces of colors and shapes you might imagine in a moment Gustav Klimt's Kiss, Ren√© Magritte's Golconde, etc. The ability of abstraction goes through the history of art and the human mind and remembers each one with hints.

To spread the vibe of my beautiful community, minters will own 50% of the royalty on each secondary sale.
Twenty-two different color palettes and three different borders with random colors are used in this artwork.
Made in p5js
Created September 2022
Artist: @ChistaAi

metadata.name: TIMEFRAMES #16
metadata.description:
‚ÄòWhat if you could take a photo of time?‚Äô

As a photographer myself, the act of taking photos is the act of freezing moments of time. Moments that will no longer ever be here. Each layer represents not only 3 aspects of time (hours, minutes and seconds) but also a very important aspect of photography: the light. Combining these two instances: the visual interpretation of light and the generative aspect of time - I present ‚ÄòTIMEFRAMES‚Äô.

12 selected colors. 5,688,900 possible combinations.

The less layers the rarer - ranging from 100% to 18%
All timeframes that have 42 on it like 4:20:00, 4:42:42, 4:20:42 are rarer - ranging from 50% to 42%
The darker the colors the rarer - ranging from 100% to 89%

Click on the image to Download. Created with @PureSpider‚Äôs template.

2022.

metadata.name: Millefoglie #403
metadata.description:
"A mille-feuille (French pronunciation: ‚Äã[mil f≈ìj], "thousand-sheets"), also known by the names Napoleon, vanilla slice, and custard slice, is a dessert made of puff pastry layered with pastry cream. Its modern form was influenced by improvements made by Marie-Antoine Car√™me.

Traditionally, a mille-feuille is made up of three layers of puff pastry (p√¢te feuillet√©e), alternating with two layers of pastry cream (cr√®me p√¢tissi√®re). The top pastry layer is finished in various ways: sometimes it is topped with whipped cream, or it may be dusted with icing sugar, cocoa, pastry crumbs, or sliced almonds. It may also be glazed with icing or fondant alone, or in alternating white (icing) and brown (chocolate) or other colored icing stripes, and combed to create a marbled effect." ‚Äî Wikipedia

metadata.name: looking through a glass #115
metadata.description:
or life is a colorful mess
or not your usual generative forest

this art project continues the path that 'life is a (beautiful) mess' began with the representation of our lives using drawing lines that make repetitive patterns
as life develops, we look at it through the glass of our unique existence. every event, emotion and thought we experience stain our personal glass and conditions our regard towards the world that surrounds us
the cercles in every composition, represents that glass that we all have between us and the world, and the movement of the lines under it, life developing as we observe it
or it's just another figurative generative art project, as you wish...

10 different palettes
over 30 different color pens
single or multiple color glasses or cercles option
press [1], [2], [3], [4] keys to multiply resolution and reload the piece
press [s] to capture an image .png
press [r] to reload the animation
click the mouse to stop the drawing
doubleclick the mouse to resume the drawing

generative art created by mehno using p5js

metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes

metadata.name: Industrial Devolution #24
metadata.description:
As the abandoned sewage planet Xnor lay seemingly dormant, aeons crept by. Erosion and oxidation recombined in plumbing, slowly causing the pipes to evolve sentience and grow to the horizon in a blooming chaos of rust, steel and concrete.

Industrial Devolution is the first long-form generative project using my rayhatching algorithm. It combines a raymarcher for SDFs with a surface orientation based flow field renderer in order to draw arbitrary 3D scenes as line art, with an organic, hatched drawing style. The SDF formulas were generatively designed and parametrized to form ancient landscapes of corroded industrial pipes and immense, ageless blocks of concrete.

The entire code of Industrial Devolution is 3930 characters, using no external libraries.

When done rendering, the output can be right-click saved as an SVG file and plotted using a plotter such as an Axidraw. The lines in the SVG are in random order, so it is recommended to use a path reordering/optimizing tool such as axicli or vpype before plotting. This will greatly reduce the plotting time. The output SVG is intended to be plotted at A3 (297x420mm) using a 0.4mm black pen (but feel free to experiment). You can change this by adding these options to the URL:

  &lw=.4 the linewidth in millimetres
  &d=.8 the line density (multiplier to the line width, density 0.6 recommended for plotter output)
  &h=420 how high the page is, in millimetres (width is always height * 0.707)
  &bg=1 set to 0 to remove background rectangle (bg=0 recommended for plotter output)

Industrial Devolution was released during a live minting event at Bright Moments Gallery, Venice Beach in collaboration with Bright Moments, fx(hash) and Tender.
